1
00:00:47,978 --> 00:00:49,376
(Sun Honglei)

2
00:00:49,792 --> 00:00:50,816
(Li Naiwen)

3
00:00:52,736 --> 00:00:54,240
(Guo Jingfei)

4
00:00:54,945 --> 00:00:56,704
(Liu Yuning)

5
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:58,752
(Gong Jun)

6
00:01:00,157 --> 00:01:00,800
(Chen Xingxu)

7
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,000
(Wang Yuwen)

8
00:01:04,392 --> 00:01:06,400
(Lin Yi)

9
00:01:09,493 --> 00:01:12,352
=Wow The World S2=

10
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:20,920
(Half of New Zealand's soul)

11
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:23,080
(lies in the icy chill of
the South Island's glaciers.)

12
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:23,880
(The other half)

13
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,760
(burns in the volcanic heat)

14
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,784
(and cultural pulse
of the North Island.)

15
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:28,360
(As the gateway to the North Island,)

16
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,800
(Auckland perfectly embodies)

17
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:32,000
(the seamless transition
between bustling city life)

18
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:32,960
(and untamed nature.)

19
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:35,560
(Today, the Earth Group heads south,)

20
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,600
(toward the cradle of Maori culture,)

21
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,592
(Rotorua,)

22
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,680
(to feel the rhythm of the land)

23
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,760
(and the breath of the earth
along the way.)

24
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,120
Hi.

25
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:45,720
=Episode 1 (Part 2)=
Morning.

26
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,840
(First Glimpse of New Zealand)
Morning.

27
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,400
Did you sleep well?

28
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,560
Still awake at 1 AM.

29
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:50,840
Your voice is much better.

30
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,480
It's much better.

31
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,720
Much better.

32
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,280
Nai, I really want to ask you something.

33
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,280
Did you do your makeup this morning?

34
00:01:59,456 --> 00:02:00,880
(Concerned)
I never wear foundation.

35
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,400
Just the hair, right?

36
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:03,880
Doing his hair.

37
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,720
Here's a 'killer' question for you.

38
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:07,080
Naiwen, isn't your hair going to

39
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,920
get thinner and thinner,

40
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,320
with all that hair gel
you use every day?

41
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,080
No, I have...

42
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,200
I have a lot of hair.

43
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:11,600
Really?

44
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,720
- A lot.
- Then let me tell you the truth.

45
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:13,720
I can see your scalp.

46
00:02:13,952 --> 00:02:14,848
(Watching the drama)

47
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,224
You mean here, right?

48
00:02:16,416 --> 00:02:17,248
I have...

49
00:02:17,248 --> 00:02:18,600
(Nai debunks the myth)
I have a scar here.

50
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,880
Let's count one, two, three by age,
the three oldest of us.

51
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,440
How about we put our heads
toward the camera

52
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,800
(You think I'm afraid of you?)
and see who's showing the most scalp?

53
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,160
Bring it on.

54
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,880
(Bring it on)
I'm definitely fine.

55
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:30,960
- Go.
- Go.

56
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,080
You used a curling iron on that.

57
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,200
And who knows
if you're wearing makeup too?

58
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:39,680
You are...

59
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,440
No electricity involved here.

60
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,080
All manual.

61
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:42,800
Alright, impressive.

62
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,160
Nothing to do with a blow dryer either.

63
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:45,600
Okay, let's get to the point.

64
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,360
This early in the morning,
meaningless "male competition."

65
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,080
Everyone,

66
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,880
today we're going to Bird Island,

67
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,280
and then from Auckland to Rotorua.

68
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:57,920
But before we set off,

69
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,040
we need to complete a mission first.

70
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,240
Let me ask you all,

71
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,920
if you had to

72
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:06,520
choose one person
you trust most during a trip,

73
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,760
who would it be?

74
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,920
I'd pick Honglei.

75
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:13,024
(Yuning's pick)

76
00:03:13,152 --> 00:03:16,832
(Solid as iron, buddies for life)

77
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:18,400
Reliable.

78
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:18,880
Honglei is reliable.

79
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:21,640
For Yuning, I'd go through fire...

80
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,040
and 'mutton soup.'

81
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:26,560
Nice.

82
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,240
Going that far for food.

83
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:28,880
That's impressive.

84
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,320
I'd pick Yuning.

85
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:32,320
That way I can have something hot
in the morning.

86
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:33,200
(Also for food)
A butler?

87
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,880
I'm mainly looking for a chef.

88
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,240
I just want to eat.

89
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,640
I'd definitely pick...

90
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,640
My first choice is Yuning.

91
00:03:42,112 --> 00:03:42,920
(Honglei's pick)

92
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,880
You two are made for each other.

93
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,120
Holding hands successfully.

94
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,880
Warming each other up.

95
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,720
(Extra)
You're the extra one.

96
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,080
When it comes to me...

97
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,720
Then I can only pick

98
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,640
your 'husband'.

99
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:56,640
Who?

100
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,984
♪Who is my bridegroom♪

101
00:04:03,854 --> 00:04:04,920
(The only one not in on it)

102
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,600
Wait.

103
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,200
Lin Yi doesn't have a clue
about any of this.

104
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:07,800
Don't.

105
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,080
(What's this, folks?)
Huh? Dating?

106
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,240
What dating?

107
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,519
We're 'dating.'

108
00:04:20,192 --> 00:04:21,800
(Really?)

109
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,600
(Fake)
Promotion for the drama?

110
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,440
The drama ended half a month ago.

111
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,480
Still promotion?

112
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,640
It's already finished airing.

113
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,680
What promotion?

114
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,360
It's an 'official announcement.'

115
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,960
Look, he's about to start roasting me.

116
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:36,800
His voice will be recovered.

117
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,480
"Get out."

118
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,000
What kind of drama is this?

119
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,240
(Just watch the main episode)
What drama?

120
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,280
I pick Jun.

121
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:45,480
(Xingxu's pick)

122
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,240
Because

123
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:48,160
I want someone to accompany me.

124
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:49,984
We can

125
00:04:49,984 --> 00:04:51,400
- No problem.
- do anything.

126
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:54,720
And you?

127
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,240
Who do you pick?

128
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,400
Nai.

129
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,680
(Jun's pick)
No problem.

130
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,560
Then I'll pick Fei.

131
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:02,680
Based on my experience
working with him yesterday,

132
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,440
he can guide me toward victory.

133
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,440
Lin Yi.

134
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,680
Write it.

135
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,680
Don't say anything.

136
00:05:12,082 --> 00:05:13,696
(Who knows it?)

137
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,800
That hurts to listen to.

138
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,280
I'd definitely pick you.

139
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,800
This fluffy guy is very smart.

140
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:20,560
How do you know?

141
00:05:22,048 --> 00:05:23,693
(My trust was wasted)

142
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,920
(Jingfei's first choice)
And well-behaved.

143
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,320
(Jingfei's second choice)
No. I was actually going to pick Gong Jun.

144
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:26,960
But since you already chose him,

145
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,200
(The real first choice)
I guess I can't really do that anymore.

146
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:29,080
Lin Yi.

147
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,440
Unreliable.

148
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,480
Unreliable.

149
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,880
I feel sorry for you.

150
00:05:38,848 --> 00:05:40,704
(Don't listen to his nonsense)

151
00:05:40,704 --> 00:05:41,840
Just now, you chose

152
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,640
the person you trust most.

153
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:44,800
Now,

154
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,880
we're going to test

155
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,280
how much you trust each other

156
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:50,160
through a mission
called "Please Go Out."

157
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,000
Once the mission begins,

158
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,240
(Rules for Please Go Out)
you should do your best

159
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,880
to stay inside this room

160
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,280
and get

161
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,320
everyone else out.

162
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,240
You can do it physically,

163
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,736
or you can talk them into leaving.

164
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,880
Got it.

165
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:05,080
(Invitation to ally) - Team up. Really.
- We three can ally together.

166
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:05,840
All four.

167
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:06,520
Let's ally together.

168
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,240
Alliance now.

169
00:06:07,488 --> 00:06:08,512
(It's starting now?)

170
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,160
(Immediate disassociation)
What's this all about?

171
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,600
Because throughout history,

172
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,440
(Jingfei's winning strategy)
going solo is a sure death.

173
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,040
You...

174
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,320
Do you trust Fei?

175
00:06:16,593 --> 00:06:17,440
(Jingfei's strict picks)

176
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,000
You three innocent kids.

177
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,560
Let's use the process of elimination.

178
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,200
We just don't be the first out.

179
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:22,920
- Right.
- Secure this first.

180
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,160
Okay.

181
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,440
(Yuning's take)
See? He picked you four

182
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,680
and kicked the four of us out first.

183
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,480
It means

184
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,400
he's got no problem taking us out,

185
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,200
and he'll do the same

186
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,000
to you three.

187
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:40,040
Plus, from what we saw last night,

188
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,440
Fei is kind of scary.

189
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,208
A bit dangerous.

190
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,320
Very dangerous.

191
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,520
Just look at what happened to Lin Yi.

192
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,480
What about me?

193
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,200
Just now Lin Yi said,
"Then I'll pick Fei."

194
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,240
(Yi's pick, Fei's pick)
Fei said, "I'd definitely pick Chen Xingxu."

195
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,440
He didn't even glance at Lin Yi.

196
00:06:55,616 --> 00:06:56,672
(Words on the tip of his tongue)

197
00:06:56,672 --> 00:06:57,696
(Then nothing)

198
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:58,680
That hurts.

199
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,040
People like that...

200
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,720
I can't take it.

201
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,760
Yesterday we were on the same team.

202
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,600
Wasn't I good to you?

203
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,480
Lin Yi, remember what just happened.

204
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:10,200
And now you're going to
team up with them against me?

205
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,600
Then give me a reason
why you didn't pick me just now.

206
00:07:18,144 --> 00:07:19,232
(Look at me, Answer me)

207
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,520
(Trying to explain)
This is a show.

208
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,632
As for everyone else, we have to...

209
00:07:21,632 --> 00:07:23,168
Throw them away.

210
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,920
Want to take him out?

211
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,880
Just want to take out Lin Yi.

212
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:29,792
(Trust crumbles)

213
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:36,160
You just spoke your true feelings.

214
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,440
All you think about
is eliminating others.

215
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,120
Wait.

216
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,160
(Yuning's take again)
For the first one to propose an alliance,

217
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,160
the rest of us form an alliance

218
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,040
and get him out. Sound good?

219
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:43,800
(Alliance fails)

220
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,200
Agreed.

221
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,080
Yes, agreed.

222
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,040
Yes, agreed.

223
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,200
Great! That's the mindset!

224
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:49,600
Very good.

225
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,320
You're excellent.

226
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,080
Really great.

227
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:52,440
Of course.

228
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,280
Good-looking and smart.

229
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:57,480
A strong person is always lonely.

230
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,320
You go out first, okay?

231
00:07:58,752 --> 00:07:59,968
(Meets a logic nemesis)

232
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,360
If we're playing it this way,

233
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:03,880
I'm in.

234
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,920
Let's carry him out first.

235
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,440
(Putting himself on the line)
And then I'll walk myself out second.

236
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,480
So cool.

237
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,080
So cool.

238
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:11,584
Can...

239
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:16,480
Can you let me finish the rules?

240
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,760
- There are more rules?
- Not finished yet.

241
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,600
Go ahead.

242
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,960
Sorry.

243
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:26,640
If you're kicked out, you're out.

244
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,800
The last person

245
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,160
still inside wins.

246
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,320
She's the only extrovert here.
[*'The last person' sounds like 'The only extrovert']

247
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,600
(E-type)
The only extrovert.

248
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,232
(Classic cliche)

249
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,039
And we're all introverts.

250
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:41,000
Here, except for Wen,
who is an extrovert,

251
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,840
are we all introverts?

252
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,640
- I'm an extrovert.
- He's an extrovert.

253
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,440
I'm an extrovert.

254
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,600
Then you go out.

255
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:47,920
The only extrovert.

256
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:48,880
You're the second extrovert.

257
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:49,520
Go out.

258
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,200
You're using this joke?

259
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,480
Forcing it, huh?

260
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,280
I think it's flawless.

261
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:02,880
No problem.

262
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,200
Listen to me.

263
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,880
Most people in this situation

264
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,760
would fight like crazy.

265
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,760
I just need to walk out with dignity.

266
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:15,720
I'll...

267
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,760
I'll do it myself.

268
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:17,760
No. Don't touch me.

269
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,880
Can you let me finish the rules?

270
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,160
Is that so?

271
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:23,320
Can we...

272
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,440
You haven't even
finished explaining the rules,

273
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,440
and we've already eliminated someone.
Is it okay?

274
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,600
That works too, actually.

275
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,440
Only one member
can be sent out at a time.

276
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,000
Anyone who is asked
to step across this line

277
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,560
is eliminated.

278
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:36,000
The last person

279
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,960
remaining inside the room

280
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:40,000
will receive a King's Card,

281
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,320
granting them special privileges

282
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,680
for the rest of the journey.

283
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,360
Okay.

284
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,240
Now we're officially starting.

285
00:09:46,432 --> 00:09:50,176
(King's Card Battle: Please Go Out)

286
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,440
Who's the first?

287
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,960
Who's the first?

288
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,320
(Pinpoint targeting)
I'll go out first.

289
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:58,760
Then you guys...

290
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,800
You stay here and...

291
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,240
Production team,
I have only one request.

292
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:01,920
When I walk out,

293
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:02,920
give me a slow-motion shot, okay?

294
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,240
Fei, do you need applause?

295
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:07,680
Alright, give me some applause.

296
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:09,120
Production team,
give me a slow-motion shot.

297
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,480
Let me leave with some dignity.

298
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:19,560
Oh, my! So handsome!

299
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,920
So cool!

300
00:10:30,112 --> 00:10:31,232
(First one kicked out)

301
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,560
He's going to eat breakfast, right?

302
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,000
(Very loudly)
I think Honglei

303
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,280
is definitely going to be carried out.

304
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,000
Because when he was young,

305
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,200
he often did this kind of thing.

306
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,160
I think that's the case.

307
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,440
(One more Yuning's take)
For the variety show effect,

308
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,760
we might have to carry him.

309
00:10:53,888 --> 00:10:55,104
(Just an excuse)

310
00:10:55,392 --> 00:10:56,800
(So this is what you were waiting for)

311
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,560
(Jun agrees)
Let's get the big brother out first.

312
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,560
Lin Yi, get off this chair.

313
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,560
(Overcoming all obstacles)
You leave this chair first.

314
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:05,344
(Locked)

315
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,040
You can't abandon me.

316
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:08,840
- I won't abandon you.
- You hear that?

317
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,640
I won't abandon you.

318
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,000
We...

319
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,680
We will stay together forever.

320
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,320
We will stay together forever.

321
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,960
Yuning, your idea is very good.

322
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,800
(Off-court guidance)
No matter what, carry him out.

323
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,600
Then let's carry
both of them out together.

324
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,720
If you're like this, hang on...

325
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,720
Wait.

326
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,680
Go ahead.

327
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:32,320
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

328
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:34,480
No!

329
00:11:36,416 --> 00:11:37,824
(The mouth is using strength too)

330
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,040
No.

331
00:11:40,192 --> 00:11:40,960
(Strength running out)

332
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:43,040
(Everyone exhausted)

333
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,480
This is no less than bungee jumping.

334
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,080
So Lin Yi, you stand up first.

335
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:46,520
Lin Yi.

336
00:11:46,786 --> 00:11:48,240
(Locked again)

337
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,240
Lin Yi, get up.

338
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:49,840
Too heavy.

339
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,400
If you get up,
it'll be easier for us to carry him.

340
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,928
Yi.

341
00:11:53,088 --> 00:11:53,664
(Tightly locked)

342
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:56,400
Lin Yi, how can you trust him?

343
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,920
Just push him away

344
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:58,840
rudely.

345
00:11:58,840 --> 00:11:59,360
Lin Yi.

346
00:12:00,352 --> 00:12:01,408
(Honglei sticks to me)

347
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,360
Just...

348
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,240
Just pry him off like that.

349
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,320
(Is it so hard to pry open?)

350
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,160
Carrying the person might be easier.

351
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:06,480
You just

352
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,480
pry him off.

353
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:08,800
Run!

354
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,360
Run, Lin Yi, trust me.

355
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,024
Lift, lift, lift! Hold it up!

356
00:12:13,824 --> 00:12:14,680
(Help who? Which side?)

357
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,600
(How to help?)
- Go. - Go.

358
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,040
Lift from that side.

359
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,480
(How to help exactly?)
Let him leave with dignity too.

360
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,840
Give me a slow-motion shot!

361
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:26,720
(Here is the slow-motion shot)

362
00:12:29,088 --> 00:12:30,304
(Get out of here)

363
00:12:32,201 --> 00:12:34,688
(Second one kicked out)

364
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,640
Liu Yuning!

365
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:42,720
You bad boy!

366
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,520
Liu Yuning!

367
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,120
Honglei, you...

368
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,600
Honglei, you...

369
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:46,200
Honglei, you now

370
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:46,760
Honglei.

371
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:56,600
No.

372
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,360
He doesn't count. He...

373
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,040
No, he doesn't count.

374
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:01,320
You...

375
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,200
You're out now.

376
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,120
They...

377
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,360
If any of them came to push me,

378
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,000
I'd accept it.

379
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,600
Then if I pull him out, does that count?

380
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,600
Any eliminated people won't count.

381
00:13:12,829 --> 00:13:15,264
(That's really a shame)

382
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,880
Now let's think backwards.

383
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,560
Who do you think

384
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,760
will be the last to stay?

385
00:13:22,208 --> 00:13:23,232
(Who can last)

386
00:13:23,232 --> 00:13:24,064
(until the end?)

387
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,280
Definitely Yuwen.

388
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:32,280
You'll definitely be the last.

389
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,880
Who would drag you out?

390
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,000
Right.

391
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:36,760
Yuwen, it's like this.

392
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:37,480
Sorry,

393
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,280
but in my logic,

394
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,400
I must carry you out.

395
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,040
Why?

396
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,240
Let's compete in something.

397
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:42,640
It's like this.

398
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,840
After I get her out,

399
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,568
I won't be a threat to you anymore.

400
00:13:46,013 --> 00:13:46,944
(After all, we already
have one King's Card)

401
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,400
So Yuwen...

402
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,040
No.

403
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:51,480
How about this?

404
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,960
After Yuwen goes out,
I'll go out right after her.

405
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,360
(Without my consent)
Why do you have to take me with you?

406
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:56,560
After he goes out,

407
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,840
I will leave gracefully myself.

408
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:58,720
You won't be able to leave gracefully.

409
00:13:58,816 --> 00:13:59,360
(Convinced by Yuning)

410
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:00,480
You won't.

411
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,480
Then you go out.

412
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:02,880
I don't want to go out.

413
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,200
Lin Yi.

414
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,240
Do you want a graceful exit,

415
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,080
or do you want...

416
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:05,720
No.

417
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,480
Wait, don't touch me.

418
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,360
(No)
No.

419
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,080
Lin Yi.

420
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:09,880
Then one by one.

421
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:10,120
Right.

422
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:10,840
(Full support)
One by one.

423
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,128
Send her away first.

424
00:14:12,128 --> 00:14:13,360
One by one.

425
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:13,880
One by one.

426
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,480
Lin Yi.

427
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,720
Lin Yi.

428
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,240
No.

429
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,440
Then you two go together.

430
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,880
You two go together.

431
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,680
Only one counts.

432
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,000
Lin Yi came out first.

433
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,840
I played myself. The clown is me.

434
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,480
I...

435
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,600
How did I get out?

436
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,360
Lin Yi.

437
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,480
No.

438
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,600
Then you two go together.

439
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,432
(First to cross the line)

440
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:00,880
Don't...

441
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:01,840
Don't have any regrets

442
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,600
and don't explain.

443
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,840
No, Lin Yi.

444
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,200
Well,

445
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:04,520
you know

446
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,000
what game we played yesterday?

447
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,720
What game?

448
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,720
Called 'Catch Me If You Can'.

449
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,080
Catch me if you can!

450
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,240
So mean!

451
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:14,960
Even making fun of him.

452
00:15:16,448 --> 00:15:18,592
(Sorry about that)

453
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,320
Yuning... I didn't expect that.

454
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:24,360
Yuning...

455
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,480
I thought in his heart,

456
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,760
after the 'sprinkling salt'
remark yesterday,

457
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,000
my status had risen a bit.

458
00:15:31,104 --> 00:15:33,184
(So mad his throat itches again)

459
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,040
(Third one kicked out)

460
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:36,000
This game... I really...

461
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,520
I never quite understood it.

462
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,000
Now I've only learned one sentence,

463
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,840
'Welcome to

464
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,960
the adult world.'

465
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,560
Yuning suddenly said
he wanted to push Yuwen out.

466
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,160
I felt something seemed off.

467
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:51,760
Then I wanted to stop Yuwen.

468
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,160
I said let's go one by one.

469
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:54,520
Then one by one...

470
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,400
I ended up being the first out.

471
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,000
Now I'm out here all by myself.

472
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,880
This game is a bit
too complicated for me.

473
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:01,640
Well...

474
00:16:02,534 --> 00:16:04,064
(Brain-burning)

475
00:16:04,512 --> 00:16:05,680
(Players remaining: 5)

476
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,920
I survived.

477
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,040
I just barely managed to survive.

478
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:08,760
(Moving)

479
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,120
Okay, good.

480
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,240
There's a first time,
but no second time.

481
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,240
Ever heard that saying?

482
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,360
Yes.

483
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,160
What are you doing?

484
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:14,640
No.

485
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,160
Sorry for the intrusion.

486
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,000
(Please spare me)
Yuning,

487
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:19,520
don't be like this.

488
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,280
Don't bully...

489
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,440
This game is just so cruel.

490
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,160
If you've got the guts,
use force to get me out.

491
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:25,880
Force can definitely get you out,

492
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,440
but I don't want it
to be so undignified.

493
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:29,520
We are all decent artists.

494
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:30,680
(Need some dignity)

495
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:31,520
Decent artists.

496
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,760
How about, if we really can't hold on,

497
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:36,880
we compete in something?

498
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:38,040
Why didn't we compete when I was here?

499
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,120
I just said let's compete.

500
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,880
You didn't speak up.

501
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,560
When you were here,

502
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:44,880
we competed on who has a louder voice.

503
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:46,848
(Quiet-voiced individual)

504
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:47,640
Shouldn't we

505
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,040
get the two of them out first?

506
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:50,240
(Suddenly being called out)

507
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,280
She wants to get us two out.

508
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:53,160
What did she say?

509
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:53,760
(Listen to my excuse)
- Get us two out. - No.

510
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:54,680
You didn't hear it.

511
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,520
I'm telling you, we can get her...

512
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,280
(Caught off guard)
You're definitely going out.

513
00:16:58,280 --> 00:16:59,240
You're definitely going out.

514
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:00,640
Liu Yuning!

515
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,000
Definitely going out!

516
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:05,240
Liu Yuning, you're not graceful at all.

517
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,520
I don't want it to be so undignified.

518
00:17:09,141 --> 00:17:10,280
(Fourth one kicked out)

519
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,520
Liu Yuning.

520
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,680
I think

521
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,400
I can get Yuning out.

522
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,400
You just went out.

523
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,400
Cool down for a bit.

524
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,400
Calm down.

525
00:17:22,592 --> 00:17:23,160
(Can't calm down at all)

526
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:23,920
As expected of a boss,

527
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,640
very cold.

528
00:17:28,138 --> 00:17:29,696
(I'll take it as a compliment)

529
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,040
I knew they wouldn't help me,

530
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:31,880
but I thought

531
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:32,360
they wouldn't help Yuning either.

532
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,040
I didn't expect...

533
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:33,840
Gong Jun.

534
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,240
You picked me just now.

535
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:37,760
You betrayed me.

536
00:17:38,309 --> 00:17:39,000
(Yes, indeed)

537
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,640
Shouldn't we
get the two of them out first?

538
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,760
Why are all my debts emotional ones?

539
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,040
It seems I was the one
who said it first.

540
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,240
(Players remaining: 4)

541
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,200
Letting Naiwen win

542
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,280
is not fun.

543
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,040
(Meaning: Time to ask Naiwen out)
Why?

544
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,160
I cannot...

545
00:17:56,354 --> 00:17:57,040
(Eager to try)

546
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:57,600
Let me tell you,

547
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,680
he's really too mean.

548
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,680
He actually...

549
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,040
He really is a dangerous person.

550
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:01,320
Very dangerous.

551
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,200
I'm telling you all,

552
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,160
let me...

553
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,320
Slowly, just stick his foot out.

554
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:09,480
(Holding on tight)
Show me some dignity!

555
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:10,440
Just stick his feet out.

556
00:18:17,984 --> 00:18:18,720
Xingxu.

557
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,720
Me?

558
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,480
Me?

559
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:21,960
What a show!

560
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,480
Me?

561
00:18:25,888 --> 00:18:26,944
(The sky is falling)

562
00:18:27,058 --> 00:18:28,576
(Stunned)

563
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,480
It was your foot that came out first?

564
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:32,600
