01:03:41,240 --> 01:03:42,680
You can choose first

1964
01:03:42,680 --> 01:03:43,640
your way of transportation.

1965
01:03:43,920 --> 01:03:44,520
Let's go.

1966
01:03:44,520 --> 01:03:44,920
Go.

1967
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:45,888
Go.

1968
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:48,224
We'll drive over.

1969
01:03:48,480 --> 01:03:49,248
(Road Trip Team: Guo Jingfei,
Liu Yuning, Gong Jun, Lin Yi)

1970
01:03:49,248 --> 01:03:50,752
(Backpacker Team: Sun Honglei,)
Honglei, let's switch.

1971
01:03:50,816 --> 01:03:52,000
(Li Naiwen, Chen Xingxu, Wang Yuwen)
I really want to be a backpacker.

1972
01:03:52,256 --> 01:03:52,920
(Switch Lin Yi with Sun Honglei)
Okay.

1973
01:03:58,848 --> 01:04:00,400
Come on. Let's see what our ride is.

1974
01:04:02,944 --> 01:04:03,720
What do you need?

1975
01:04:03,720 --> 01:04:04,544
We'll help you.

1976
01:04:04,544 --> 01:04:05,040
Okay.

1977
01:04:05,040 --> 01:04:06,840
Just don't turn off your phones.

1978
01:04:06,840 --> 01:04:07,360
(Care from Guo)
No problem.

1979
01:04:07,880 --> 01:04:08,608
(Trust)
Stay in touch.

1980
01:04:08,608 --> 01:04:09,200
No problem.

1981
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:10,200
Let's go.

1982
01:04:10,200 --> 01:04:10,800
Go.

1983
01:04:10,800 --> 01:04:11,320
Go.

1984
01:04:14,080 --> 01:04:15,424
Let's drive there

1985
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:16,440
to show it off.

1986
01:04:17,080 --> 01:04:17,472
Okay.

1987
01:04:17,984 --> 01:04:18,800
(Winning without showing off is a waste)
Drive over.

1988
01:04:18,800 --> 01:04:19,600
Why not?

1989
01:04:19,968 --> 01:04:20,960
Drive right in front of them.

1990
01:04:22,480 --> 01:04:23,968
Don't take a detour.

1991
01:04:23,968 --> 01:04:25,200
Just drive straight out.

1992
01:04:25,200 --> 01:04:26,720
The road is right there.

1993
01:04:26,816 --> 01:04:27,360
We're off.

1994
01:04:27,360 --> 01:04:28,120
(Showing off)

1995
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:29,000
Need a ride?

1996
01:04:29,360 --> 01:04:30,920
Hey, fellow locals.

1997
01:04:31,840 --> 01:04:32,832
(Jealous?)
I'm a little happy.

1998
01:04:33,280 --> 01:04:35,080
This AC is freezing.

1999
01:04:35,264 --> 01:04:36,672
Taking the bus?

2000
01:04:36,992 --> 01:04:38,480
Have a great trip.

2001
01:04:38,480 --> 01:04:40,032
(Showing off)

2002
01:04:40,240 --> 01:04:41,344
We're leaving! Bye-bye.

2003
01:04:41,344 --> 01:04:42,040
Bye-bye.

2004
01:04:42,040 --> 01:04:42,960
(Totally not care)
Drive safely.

2005
01:04:42,960 --> 01:04:43,904
Be careful.

2006
01:04:44,120 --> 01:04:45,480
Watch the road.

2007
01:04:45,888 --> 01:04:46,848
Watch the road.

2008
01:04:47,040 --> 01:04:48,840
Don't show off. Be safe.

2009
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:49,360
Be careful.

2010
01:04:49,360 --> 01:04:50,000
Alright.

2011
01:04:50,400 --> 01:04:51,000
(4 hours until the agreed dinner time)
Let's go.

2012
01:04:51,000 --> 01:04:51,480
Let's set off.

2013
01:04:52,920 --> 01:04:54,000
Let's find some shade.

2014
01:04:58,528 --> 01:04:59,936
Walking is actually really nice.

2015
01:04:59,936 --> 01:05:00,480
Yes.

2016
01:05:00,480 --> 01:05:00,920
Right.

2017
01:05:00,920 --> 01:05:01,920
How comfortable.

2018
01:05:02,368 --> 01:05:03,168
Let's walk.

2019
01:05:03,168 --> 01:05:04,400
Just like a spring outing.

2020
01:05:05,120 --> 01:05:06,480
Let's take a photo

2021
01:05:06,480 --> 01:05:07,920
like this sign.

2022
01:05:08,576 --> 01:05:10,280
It's the sign of school.

2023
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:12,480
We hold hands.

2024
01:05:12,480 --> 01:05:13,056
Right.

2025
01:05:13,200 --> 01:05:14,040
Going on an outing.

2026
01:05:26,240 --> 01:05:27,360
Okay.

2027
01:05:27,360 --> 01:05:28,000
That's enough.

2028
01:05:29,344 --> 01:05:30,240
(Here comes the target)

2029
01:05:31,813 --> 01:05:32,864
(Whizzing by)

2030
01:05:33,728 --> 01:05:34,560
This car is too small.

2031
01:05:34,880 --> 01:05:36,192
(Picky)

2032
01:05:38,960 --> 01:05:39,720
Not this one.

2033
01:05:39,720 --> 01:05:40,320
Too small.

2034
01:05:40,320 --> 01:05:41,560
(Can't fit four people)
Not this one.

2035
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:43,600
(One on board is better than none)
We're lucky if they even stop.

2036
01:05:48,148 --> 01:05:49,160
(Two targets)

2037
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:49,720
This one.

2038
01:05:49,720 --> 01:05:50,760
I want the one behind.

2039
01:05:51,600 --> 01:05:52,480
Will it stop for us?

2040
01:05:52,480 --> 01:05:54,040
Hey, you're getting picky.

2041
01:05:54,040 --> 01:05:55,200
Will they even stop?

2042
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:58,080
(Failed)

2043
01:05:58,624 --> 01:05:59,104
(Trying hard)

2044
01:05:59,104 --> 01:06:00,192
Is it because you didn't smile?

2045
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:01,480
I smiled.

2046
01:06:01,728 --> 01:06:02,816
Is it because I'm here?

2047
01:06:02,816 --> 01:06:03,600
Come on, switch.

2048
01:06:04,320 --> 01:06:05,040
I'll stand second.

2049
01:06:05,480 --> 01:06:06,368
(Good looks strategy)
Let's change our front face.

2050
01:06:06,592 --> 01:06:07,712
(Greeting with a smile)

2051
01:06:08,960 --> 01:06:09,632
(Failed again)

2052
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:11,120
Lin Yi, you go in front.

2053
01:06:11,424 --> 01:06:12,448
(Change the front face again)

2054
01:06:12,704 --> 01:06:14,304
(Sincere)

2055
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:16,864
(Empty)

2056
01:06:17,000 --> 01:06:18,600
As soon as I stand here,
no cars are even coming.

2057
01:06:20,480 --> 01:06:21,160
Stop this one?

2058
01:06:21,856 --> 01:06:23,280
Yes. Stop any that come.

2059
01:06:26,134 --> 01:06:26,880
(Failed again)

2060
01:06:26,880 --> 01:06:27,720
Great.

2061
01:06:28,640 --> 01:06:29,600
Can this one fit us?

2062
01:06:31,680 --> 01:06:32,544
(Got a response)

2063
01:06:33,056 --> 01:06:33,888
(There's hope)

2064
01:06:35,680 --> 01:06:37,240
(Failed again)

2065
01:06:37,240 --> 01:06:38,680
Why did he give us this gesture?

2066
01:06:38,680 --> 01:06:39,600
They're returning the thumbs-up.

2067
01:06:39,880 --> 01:06:40,992
Did we give the wrong gesture?

2068
01:06:40,992 --> 01:06:42,080
Should it be like this?

2069
01:06:42,592 --> 01:06:44,768
(Miserable and desolate)

2070
01:06:44,960 --> 01:06:47,168
(No cars at all)

2071
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:48,640
We'll have to wait a bit.

2072
01:06:49,120 --> 01:06:51,520
(3.5 hours until the agreed dinner time)

2073
01:06:53,856 --> 01:06:55,440
So cozy.

2074
01:06:57,280 --> 01:06:58,120
A gentle breeze blows.

2075
01:06:58,760 --> 01:07:00,240
That feels great.

2076
01:07:05,376 --> 01:07:07,840
♪Growin like a breeze♪

2077
01:07:07,968 --> 01:07:10,400
♪Country roads♪

2078
01:07:10,720 --> 01:07:13,632
♪Take me home♪

2079
01:07:13,952 --> 01:07:16,200
♪To the place I belong♪

2080
01:07:16,200 --> 01:07:16,800
Happy.

2081
01:07:19,520 --> 01:07:22,112
♪West Virginia♪

2082
01:07:22,528 --> 01:07:24,928
♪Mountain Momma♪

2083
01:07:25,376 --> 01:07:28,256
♪Take me home♪

2084
01:07:28,256 --> 01:07:31,232
♪Country roads♪

2085
01:07:31,456 --> 01:07:32,800
(Their singing drifts
through every bit of the scenery)

2086
01:07:32,800 --> 01:07:33,280
Cozy.

2087
01:07:33,280 --> 01:07:35,072
(All the warmth and comfort of the trip
is hidden along the way)

2088
01:07:35,680 --> 01:07:37,160
Have you seen a meme of a car?

2089
01:07:37,160 --> 01:07:39,040
The one with Jim Carrey.

2090
01:07:39,040 --> 01:07:39,480
Like this.

2091
01:07:40,960 --> 01:07:41,184
Right.

2092
01:07:41,856 --> 01:07:42,368
That one.

2093
01:07:42,496 --> 01:07:43,040
Let's do that.

2094
01:07:43,040 --> 01:07:43,440
They were driving.

2095
01:07:43,600 --> 01:07:44,360
Come on.

2096
01:07:44,920 --> 01:07:45,600
One, two.

2097
01:07:45,600 --> 01:07:47,808
Come on, one, two, three, go.

2098
01:07:47,960 --> 01:07:49,520
Right, left.

2099
01:07:50,592 --> 01:07:51,080
I can't.

2100
01:07:51,080 --> 01:07:51,920
I have to drive carefully.

2101
01:07:51,920 --> 01:07:52,800
You need to drive properly.

2102
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:54,080
Don't sway. We'll sway.

2103
01:07:54,080 --> 01:07:55,080
I'm swaying a bit too much.

2104
01:07:56,840 --> 01:07:58,840
Look at these cars on the road.

2105
01:07:58,840 --> 01:07:59,720
The traffic.

2106
01:08:00,512 --> 01:08:02,040
How could they get a ride?

2107
01:08:02,400 --> 01:08:03,840
(Worry)
I think it'll be hard for them.

2108
01:08:04,512 --> 01:08:05,248
They'll have a tough time.

2109
01:08:05,248 --> 01:08:06,520
For example,

2110
01:08:06,520 --> 01:08:07,520
if two people are in a car,

2111
01:08:07,520 --> 01:08:08,576
the back can't fit four.

2112
01:08:08,576 --> 01:08:09,040
Right?

2113
01:08:09,040 --> 01:08:10,840
They can't stop a sedan.

2114
01:08:10,840 --> 01:08:12,480
From my understanding of Naiwen,

2115
01:08:12,480 --> 01:08:13,160
he...

2116
01:08:13,160 --> 01:08:14,480
His English's not good.

2117
01:08:14,480 --> 01:08:15,296
He'll pretend not to understand.

2118
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:16,720
Pretend he can't speak.

2119
01:08:16,720 --> 01:08:18,680
Once on board, he'll have a heart attack
and faint,

2120
01:08:19,136 --> 01:08:21,479
and then they'll take him
to the hospital.

2121
01:08:22,720 --> 01:08:23,399
How about this?

2122
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:24,479
I'll pretend to faint.

2123
01:08:25,664 --> 01:08:26,800
(Even such an unusual plan is predicted)
We'll do first aid by the roadside.

2124
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:28,120
Soon an ambulance will come.

2125
01:08:28,224 --> 01:08:29,920
(Bitter smile)
Then I'll just call you an ambulance.

2126
01:08:30,720 --> 01:08:32,399
No hope at all.

2127
01:08:32,399 --> 01:08:33,440
There are no cars.

2128
01:08:33,696 --> 01:08:34,656
(3 hours until dinner time)

2129
01:08:34,656 --> 01:08:34,960
I...

2130
01:08:34,960 --> 01:08:35,488
I...

2131
01:08:35,920 --> 01:08:37,359
Am I so lucky?

2132
01:08:38,200 --> 01:08:38,816
This car's big.

2133
01:08:44,279 --> 01:08:46,160
Do you want to ride in this car?

2134
01:08:48,399 --> 01:08:49,536
Is that a garbage truck?

2135
01:08:52,800 --> 01:08:53,479
(Hello. Goodbye)

2136
01:08:53,479 --> 01:08:55,600
Every driver is smiling happily.

2137
01:08:56,040 --> 01:08:57,359
No hope at all.

2138
01:09:00,064 --> 01:09:01,120
Have a nice day.

2139
01:09:02,920 --> 01:09:04,359
Did you all drive?

2140
01:09:06,016 --> 01:09:06,624
Cheers.

2141
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:07,392
What to do?

2142
01:09:07,600 --> 01:09:10,176
Can we still make our 8 p.m. dinner?

2143
01:09:10,272 --> 01:09:11,520
There's a supermarket ahead.

2144
01:09:11,840 --> 01:09:12,720
Let's go.

2145
01:09:13,479 --> 01:09:14,640
The weather here is unpredictable.

2146
01:09:14,640 --> 01:09:15,680
Let's buy two umbrellas.

2147
01:09:16,439 --> 01:09:16,979
Hello.

2148
01:09:16,979 --> 01:09:17,760
Hello.

2149
01:09:17,760 --> 01:09:19,279
I want to buy some ice cream.

2150
01:09:19,712 --> 01:09:20,279
Thank you.

2151
01:09:22,040 --> 01:09:24,448
Sun Honglei is just a driver.

2152
01:09:24,800 --> 01:09:26,040
Does he get such treatment?

2153
01:09:26,040 --> 01:09:27,104
(Showing off)

2154
01:09:27,800 --> 01:09:28,560
Traveling

2155
01:09:29,479 --> 01:09:30,720
is about enjoying the process.

2156
01:09:34,880 --> 01:09:36,224
Slow down the pace.

2157
01:09:37,280 --> 01:09:39,680
You'll have more time and space

2158
01:09:40,256 --> 01:09:41,160
to take in

2159
01:09:42,279 --> 01:09:43,560
the beautiful scenery around you.

2160
01:09:43,560 --> 01:09:44,439
(Traveling is about
enjoying the process.)

2161
01:09:44,439 --> 01:09:45,024
(Slow down the pace)
Car?

2162
01:09:45,024 --> 01:09:45,680
(Only then do you have
the time and space)

2163
01:09:45,680 --> 01:09:46,720
(to take in the beautiful scenery)
Cars are everywhere,

2164
01:09:46,720 --> 01:09:47,240
(Li Naiwen)

2165
01:09:47,240 --> 01:09:47,720
right?

2166
01:09:48,600 --> 01:09:49,600
In the car,

2167
01:09:49,600 --> 01:09:50,240
I guess,

2168
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:52,479
they're just chatting boringly,

2169
01:09:53,472 --> 01:09:54,480
before falling asleep.

2170
01:09:55,328 --> 01:09:56,864
Maybe he's even tired.

2171
01:09:57,152 --> 01:09:58,976
(Tired)

2172
01:09:59,142 --> 01:10:00,544
(Predicted precisely again)

2173
01:10:00,608 --> 01:10:02,200
Let's call Jingfei now.

2174
01:10:04,416 --> 01:10:04,960
Hi.

2175
01:10:06,040 --> 01:10:06,720
How are you guys?

2176
01:10:07,360 --> 01:10:08,416
We're eating ice cream.

2177
01:10:10,176 --> 01:10:11,240
It's obviously because you

2178
01:10:11,240 --> 01:10:12,840
didn't get a ride, right?

2179
01:10:13,360 --> 01:10:14,600
(Arguing back and forth)
We could, but we chose not to.

2180
01:10:15,560 --> 01:10:16,040
So many cars.

2181
01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:16,840
Oh, so impressive.

2182
01:10:16,840 --> 01:10:18,816
We're sending our regards to you.

2183
01:10:18,816 --> 01:10:19,552
How are you?

2184
01:10:19,840 --> 01:10:20,544
Are you tired?

2185
01:10:20,920 --> 01:10:22,760
They went into the supermarket
to buy stuff.

2186
01:10:22,760 --> 01:10:23,840
(So free and easy?)
And we drove

2187
01:10:23,840 --> 01:10:24,920
very, very happily,

2188
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:25,680
listening to music.

2189
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:26,560
Wait,

2190
01:10:27,040 --> 01:10:28,040
what are they buying?

2191
01:10:29,504 --> 01:10:31,040
(Activating shopping mode)
This looks delicious, Yuning.

2192
01:10:31,040 --> 01:10:31,680
This is spicy.

2193
01:10:31,808 --> 01:10:32,768
These apples are good.

2194
01:10:33,568 --> 01:10:34,400
The ice cream in this freezer

2195
01:10:34,400 --> 01:10:35,520
is quite awesome.

2196
01:10:35,920 --> 01:10:36,864
Let's buy this, exactly four.

2197
01:10:37,160 --> 01:10:37,720
Hazelnut flavor.

2198
01:10:37,720 --> 01:10:38,080
Okay.

2199
01:10:39,040 --> 01:10:40,224
Take it.

2200
01:10:40,440 --> 01:10:40,880
Alright.

2201
01:10:41,480 --> 01:10:42,496
Hey, what is this?

2202
01:10:42,496 --> 01:10:43,040
Look.

2203
01:10:43,040 --> 01:10:44,320
Buy it if you want it. It's fine.

2204
01:10:44,320 --> 01:10:44,680
Buy it.

2205
01:10:44,680 --> 01:10:45,000
Yes.

2206
01:10:45,000 --> 01:10:45,320
Snacks.

2207
01:10:45,320 --> 01:10:45,720
Have a taste.

2208
01:10:45,720 --> 01:10:46,600
If we don't have enough at checkout,

2209
01:10:46,600 --> 01:10:47,520
we'll just leave you as collateral.

2210
01:10:47,872 --> 01:10:48,680
Thanks a lot.

2211
01:10:49,120 --> 01:10:50,600
(That show-off just now was like a joke)

2212
01:10:50,600 --> 01:10:51,520
I can see

2213
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:52,600
your current frame, you know?

2214
01:10:52,600 --> 01:10:53,160
Naiwen,

2215
01:10:53,160 --> 01:10:55,120
you're standing by the roadside
with nothing.

2216
01:10:55,120 --> 01:10:55,560
Right?

2217
01:10:55,560 --> 01:10:56,240
The four of you.

2218
01:10:56,800 --> 01:10:57,800
You're such a liar.

2219
01:10:57,800 --> 01:10:58,680
Eating ice cream?

2220
01:10:58,680 --> 01:10:59,040
Stop lying.

2221
01:10:59,040 --> 01:11:00,560
After I hang up, I'll send you a photo.

2222
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:01,480
You don't believe me?

2223
01:11:06,624 --> 01:11:08,640
(Send a photo to provoke)

2224
01:11:08,840 --> 01:11:09,360
What about now?

2225
01:11:12,800 --> 01:11:14,464
(He actually got to eat it)

2226
01:11:14,720 --> 01:11:16,128
(Encountered Chinese people)
Honglei, drive safely.

2227
01:11:16,128 --> 01:11:17,040
Okay.

2228
01:11:17,040 --> 01:11:18,144
Happy New Year.

2229
01:11:18,800 --> 01:11:19,480
Did you buy food?

2230
01:11:19,840 --> 01:11:20,440
Yes.

2231
01:11:20,440 --> 01:11:21,056
I bought some for you.

2232
01:11:21,056 --> 01:11:23,072
Naiwen and the others
are eating ice cream.

2233
01:11:23,072 --> 01:11:23,680
He just sent me a message.

2234
01:11:23,920 --> 01:11:24,960
They're eating too?

2235
01:11:24,960 --> 01:11:25,560
Yes.

2236
01:11:25,920 --> 01:11:27,120
We were thinking of giving these

2237
01:11:27,120 --> 01:11:28,760
to those we hitch a ride with.

2238
01:11:28,760 --> 01:11:29,536
(Selected gifts)

2239
01:11:29,536 --> 01:11:30,120
Okay.

2240
01:11:30,120 --> 01:11:31,280
We picked the two biggest ones,

2241
01:11:31,280 --> 01:11:32,440
(Dignified)
the ones that show sincerity the most.

2242
01:11:33,400 --> 01:11:33,800
Lin Yi.

2243
01:11:34,464 --> 01:11:36,032
Is it possible for you

2244
01:11:36,240 --> 01:11:37,696
to call Fei back to pick you up?

2245
01:11:37,960 --> 01:11:38,440
Just say that you are

2246
01:11:38,440 --> 01:11:39,872
both from Yi Guo Duo.
For old times' sake.

2247
01:11:40,360 --> 01:11:41,320
There is a problem.

2248
01:11:41,320 --> 01:11:43,080
If he comes back, only I can get on.

2249
01:11:43,560 --> 01:11:44,768
Can I leave you behind?

2250
01:11:45,560 --> 01:11:47,880
Even if he gets off,
there's only one spot empty.

2251
01:11:48,512 --> 01:11:49,664
He definitely won't get off.

2252
01:11:50,200 --> 01:11:50,840
Make a video call.

2253
01:11:55,168 --> 01:11:56,736
He can at least come over
and think of something.

2254
01:11:58,040 --> 01:11:58,680
Steelie.

2255
01:12:00,256 --> 01:12:00,928
(Hangs up)

2256
01:12:02,944 --> 01:12:04,080
He hung up?

2257
01:12:04,256 --> 01:12:05,960
(Shocked)

2258
01:12:06,144 --> 01:12:07,240
He hung up on me.

2259
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:08,160
(False alarm)

2260
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:08,800
Hello?

2261
01:12:09,920 --> 01:12:10,520
Fei?

2262
01:12:11,168 --> 01:12:11,800
Steelie?

2263
01:12:12,200 --> 01:12:12,920
We're in trouble.

2264
01:12:12,920 --> 01:12:14,016
(Putting on an act)
Something's wrong.

2265
01:12:14,016 --> 01:12:15,712
This is an emergency.

2266
01:12:15,968 --> 01:12:17,440
You need to come back and help me.

2267
01:12:18,160 --> 01:12:19,160
Okay, fine.

2268
01:12:19,160 --> 01:12:19,800
(Both show off acting)
No problem.

2269
01:12:19,800 --> 01:12:20,560
Where are you?

2270
01:12:20,560 --> 01:12:21,680
I'm at this...

2271
01:12:21,680 --> 01:12:22,440
Where am I?

2272
01:12:22,800 --> 01:12:24,440
I'm at...

2273
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:25,560
I'll send you my location.

2274
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:26,960
We can't get a ride.

2275
01:12:27,880 --> 01:12:29,200
No problem, my King.

2276
01:12:29,200 --> 01:12:31,440
Our car can fit a lot of people.

2277
01:12:32,320 --> 01:12:33,000
Really?

2278
01:12:33,216 --> 01:12:34,000
We'll come pick you up.

2279
01:12:34,240 --> 01:12:35,200
Give me the address.

2280
01:12:35,264 --> 01:12:37,280
(Excited)
You are so reliable, Steelie.

2281
01:12:37,640 --> 01:12:38,272
Okay.

2282
01:12:38,432 --> 01:12:39,080
See you in a bit.

2283
01:12:40,080 --> 01:12:41,120
Waiting for you guys.
I'll send you the location.

2284
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:41,840
Love you.

2285
01:12:42,080 --> 01:12:42,680
Wait, no.

2286
01:12:42,680 --> 01:12:43,920
When will they come?

2287
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:45,664
What do you mean "in a bit"?

2288
01:12:46,080 --> 01:12:46,920
Just in a bit.

2289
01:12:47,232 --> 01:12:48,160
Hello?

2290
01:12:48,160 --> 01:12:49,440
(Every thing gets a response,
but nothing gets done)

2291
01:12:49,440 --> 01:12:52,160
"In a bit" means let's eat
something first, of course.

2292
01:12:52,160 --> 01:12:53,040
Don't they think

2293
01:12:53,040 --> 01:12:54,560
that all this is going too smoothly?

2294
01:12:55,320 --> 01:12:56,160
(Blind trust)
He's my good friend.

2295
01:12:56,160 --> 01:12:56,928
Would he not listen to me?

2296
01:12:56,928 --> 01:12:57,536
"See you in a bit"

2297
01:12:57,536 --> 01:12:58,800
might mean

2298
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:00,240
we can see them
after we figure out how to get there.

2299
01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:00,920
Lin Yi,

2300
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:02,656
have you thought about something?

2301
01:13:03,136 --> 01:13:05,056
(Seeing through everything)
The steering wheel isn't in his hands.

2302
01:13:06,200 --> 01:13:07,320
He still has to get out of the car,

2303
01:13:07,320 --> 01:13:09,440
open the door, and walk toward me.

2304
01:13:09,632 --> 01:13:10,720
I'm his good friend.

2305
01:13:10,944 --> 01:13:12,544
He definitely won't do that.

2306
01:13:12,960 --> 01:13:14,880
Well, he should have given me some
emotional support just now.

2307
01:13:15,424 --> 01:13:16,448
Give me a little hope.

2308
01:13:16,600 --> 01:13:18,040
Didn't he give you emotional support?

2309
01:13:18,040 --> 01:13:18,640
He said "Okay".

2310
01:13:18,640 --> 01:13:19,560
"Okay, coming right away."

2311
01:13:19,560 --> 01:13:21,160
"I'll be there. See you in a bit."

2312
01:13:21,160 --> 01:13:21,880
He only provided emotional support.

2313
01:13:21,880 --> 01:13:23,552
He also said
"Our car can fit a lot of people."

2314
01:13:23,552 --> 01:13:24,864
He gave you hope.

2315
01:13:25,344 --> 01:13:27,264
(Don't underestimate our bond)

2316
01:13:27,360 --> 01:13:28,768
If you don't come over,

2317
01:13:29,000 --> 01:13:30,120
think about the consequences.

2318
01:13:31,008 --> 01:13:32,320
No, no need to threaten him.

2319
01:13:32,960 --> 01:13:33,880
(Trusting the friendship of Yi Guo duo)
My phone call will work.

2320
01:13:34,368 --> 01:13:34,960
Alright.

2321
01:13:34,960 --> 01:13:35,712
My word is law.

2322
01:13:37,960 --> 01:13:38,480
Honey,

2323
01:13:39,320 --> 01:13:41,344
they want us to go back

2324
01:13:41,440 --> 01:13:42,240
and pick them up.

2325
01:13:42,240 --> 01:13:43,648
I agreed without hesitation.

2326
01:13:43,648 --> 01:13:44,480
But I believe

2327
01:13:44,480 --> 01:13:45,240
that not a single one of us

2328
01:13:45,240 --> 01:13:46,720
is willing to go back and get them.

2329
01:13:46,720 --> 01:13:47,600
There's no space.

2330
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:48,360
Only the trunk is empty.

2331
01:13:48,360 --> 01:13:49,480
It's not about space.

2332
01:13:49,480 --> 01:13:50,200
I think

2333
01:13:51,000 --> 01:13:52,080
it's not about friendship either.

2334
01:13:52,080 --> 01:13:53,184
We love them very much.

2335
01:13:53,312 --> 01:13:55,440
But these are the rules
of the game, right?

2336
01:13:55,440 --> 01:13:55,680
Exactly.

2337
01:13:55,680 --> 01:13:57,400
They chose to take this path.

2338
01:13:57,400 --> 01:14:00,200
(Casually feeding him)
How can we let them break the rules?

2339
01:14:00,200 --> 01:14:00,736
Exactly.

2340
01:14:00,736 --> 01:14:01,360
Seriously.

2341
01:14:01,840 --> 01:14:02,560
Come on, cheers.

2342
01:14:02,760 --> 01:14:03,520
Cheers.

2343
01:14:03,584 --> 01:14:05,080
Cheers.

2344
01:14:05,568 --> 01:14:06,240
So happy.

2345
01:14:07,840 --> 01:14:08,864
They're checking you out, Yuning.

2346
01:14:09,056 --> 01:14:10,200
Smiling at you, Yuning.

2347
01:14:12,160 --> 01:14:12,896
Falling in love with you.

2348
01:14:13,360 --> 01:14:13,920
That's normal.

2349
01:14:19,240 --> 01:14:21,024
It's not every day that
we get to have Honglei drive

2350
01:14:21,024 --> 01:14:22,592
and take us for a ride?

2351
01:14:22,592 --> 01:14:23,424
You're so right.

2352
01:14:23,616 --> 01:14:24,160
Right?

2353
01:14:24,160 --> 01:14:25,720
Our bond, let me tell you,

2354
01:14:26,240 --> 01:14:26,880
is quite rare.

2355
01:14:26,880 --> 01:14:28,512
It takes a hundred years of cultivation
to cross the same river in a boat.

2356
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:29,200
You know that?

2357
01:14:29,200 --> 01:14:30,080
We're like on the same boat now.

2358
01:14:30,080 --> 01:14:31,280
This means so much more

2359
01:14:31,280 --> 01:14:32,200
than on the same boat.

2360
01:14:32,200 --> 01:14:32,760
Right.

2361
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:33,440
So rare.

2362
01:14:37,568 --> 01:14:38,368
Steelie.

2363
01:14:39,648 --> 01:14:40,560
(2 hours until agreed dinner time)

2364
01:14:40,560 --> 01:14:42,912
If we can't get a ride soon,
we'll miss dinner.

2365
01:14:42,912 --> 01:14:43,760
This car is leaving.

2366
01:14:43,760 --> 01:14:44,560
Is he leaving?

2367
01:14:45,000 --> 01:14:45,664
Hi.

2368
01:14:46,760 --> 01:14:48,120
Can I talk with you?

2369
01:14:48,120 --> 01:14:49,120
Yeah, sure.

2370
01:14:49,120 --> 01:14:50,280
We're from China.

2371
01:14:50,280 --> 01:14:50,920
Hi.

2372
01:14:50,920 --> 01:14:54,464
We want to go to this place.

2373
01:14:54,784 --> 01:14:56,448
Could you give us a ride?

2374
01:14:56,800 --> 01:14:59,200
I'm familiar with every street,
but not this one.

2375
01:14:59,200 --> 01:15:00,120
(Not familiar)
Okay.

2376
01:15:00,120 --> 01:15:01,720
Yeah, sorry about that.

2377
01:15:01,720 --> 01:15:03,264
Thank you. I'm sorry.

2378
01:15:04,032 --> 01:15:05,056
There's another car leaving here.

2379
01:15:05,280 --> 01:15:05,920
Let's ask them.

2380
01:15:06,600 --> 01:15:07,328
Hi.

2381
01:15:07,800 --> 01:15:09,280
We want to go here.

2382
01:15:09,520 --> 01:15:10,760
(Still has work, can't give a ride)
I have to get back to work.

2383
01:15:10,760 --> 01:15:11,520
Okay.

2384
01:15:11,520 --> 01:15:12,320
Have a nice day.

2385
01:15:13,408 --> 01:15:14,200
He said he has

2386
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:15,480
to work.

2387
01:15:15,480 --> 01:15:16,040
Okay.

2388
01:15:16,640 --> 01:15:17,520
This one is leaving too.

2389
01:15:18,160 --> 01:15:18,920
It doesn't have space

2390
01:15:18,920 --> 01:15:19,800
in the back.

2391
01:15:20,224 --> 01:15:21,184
(Can't take extra passengers)
It's a truck.

2392
01:15:21,184 --> 01:15:22,240
Yeah, it's full.

2393
01:15:22,800 --> 01:15:24,040
It's okay, let's wait for Steelie.

2394
01:15:24,448 --> 01:15:26,688
Steelie said he'd be here soon.

2395
01:15:26,784 --> 01:15:27,800
Do you believe him?

2396
01:15:27,800 --> 01:15:28,400
I do.

2397
01:15:28,400 --> 01:15:29,504
(Sincere)

2398
01:15:29,800 --> 01:15:31,120
There's no point
in lying to me about this.

2399
01:15:31,120 --> 01:15:33,280
And he said you guys
must not take a ride.

2400
01:15:33,280 --> 01:15:34,368
We'll be there soon.

2401
01:15:34,400 --> 01:15:35,760
Then I don't believe it.

2402
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:37,440
(Silence)

2403
01:15:41,216 --> 01:15:42,400
(Stop please)

2404
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:44,760
Don't just say hello.

2405
01:15:45,952 --> 01:15:48,000
They all politely said

2406
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:48,864
"Hi" to me.

2407
01:15:53,824 --> 01:15:54,480
Their horn.

2408
01:15:55,880 --> 01:15:56,720
It sounded kind of nice though.

2409
01:16:06,120 --> 01:16:07,000
Hi.

2410
01:16:07,000 --> 01:16:09,120
(Successfully stopped a car)

2411
01:16:09,120 --> 01:16:10,496
Thank you very much.

2412
01:16:11,400 --> 01:16:12,000
Hello.

2413
01:16:12,000 --> 01:16:13,000
Hello.

2414
01:16:13,000 --> 01:16:14,080
Oh, you speak Chinese?

2415
01:16:14,080 --> 01:16:14,840
Yes, we do.

2416
01:16:14,840 --> 01:16:15,840
Do you recognize us?

2417
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:16,520
(Meeting Chinese)
Yes.

2418
01:16:16,520 --> 01:16:17,360
That makes it easier.

2419
01:16:17,360 --> 01:16:18,112
Thank you.

2420
01:16:18,112 --> 01:16:19,040
Naiwen, come over and smile.

2421
01:16:19,072 --> 01:16:19,840
Is it convenient?

2422
01:16:20,280 --> 01:16:20,760
What?

2423
01:16:21,248 --> 01:16:21,920
Naiwen.

2424
01:16:21,920 --> 01:16:22,816
This is Li Naiwen.

2425
01:16:22,816 --> 01:16:23,840
Hi.

2426
01:16:23,840 --> 01:16:24,520
Do you know him?

2427
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:24,832
Hi.

2428
01:16:24,832 --> 01:16:26,360
Hello.

2429
01:16:26,360 --> 01:16:26,640
Here's the thing,

2430
01:16:26,640 --> 01:16:28,320
we need a ride

2431
01:16:28,560 --> 01:16:30,920
to the restaurant we're heading to.

2432
01:16:31,136 --> 01:16:32,096
So we need a lift.

2433
01:16:32,096 --> 01:16:32,960
But along the way,

2434
01:16:32,960 --> 01:16:34,800
no one has stopped for us.

2435
01:16:35,200 --> 01:16:35,640
Well, get in.

2436
01:16:35,640 --> 01:16:36,400
Get in.

2437
01:16:36,400 --> 01:16:36,920
We can't fit.

2438
01:16:36,920 --> 01:16:37,720
(Not enough seats)

2439
01:16:37,720 --> 01:16:38,464
There's a baby.

2440
01:16:44,200 --> 01:16:44,640
Alright then.

2441
01:16:44,640 --> 01:16:46,400
I'll stay with Lin Yi
and wait for his Steelie.

2442
01:16:46,784 --> 01:16:47,680
You two can go first.

2443
01:16:47,840 --> 01:16:48,320
That works too.

2444
01:16:48,320 --> 01:16:48,704
Okay.

2445
01:16:48,928 --> 01:16:49,560
Okay.

2446
01:16:49,800 --> 01:16:50,432
(Departing in groups)
Then, okay.

2447
01:16:50,640 --> 01:16:51,200
Then we...

2448
01:16:51,200 --> 01:16:51,880
Then we...

2449
01:16:51,880 --> 01:16:52,960
Can we get in?

2450
01:16:52,960 --> 01:16:54,160
Sure.

2451
01:16:54,560 --> 01:16:55,720
Sorry for the trouble.

2452
01:16:55,840 --> 01:16:56,640
Thank you.

2453
01:17:02,027 --> 01:17:04,032
(Li Naiwen and Chen Xingxu
successfully hitched a ride)

2454
01:17:04,096 --> 01:17:04,768
Don't wait for Steelie.

2455
01:17:04,768 --> 01:17:06,144
Once they leave,
we'll flag down another car.

2456
01:17:06,144 --> 01:17:07,008
Then we'll go too.

2457
01:17:07,120 --> 01:17:07,872
Look,

2458
01:17:08,240 --> 01:17:09,824
it's been a long time

2459
01:17:09,824 --> 01:17:11,200
since he said he was almost here.

2460
01:17:11,600 --> 01:17:13,360
(Love, trust, and wait)
Steelie.

2461
01:17:13,360 --> 01:17:14,280
This is King.

2462
01:17:15,320 --> 01:17:16,200
Are you here yet?

2463
01:17:19,640 --> 01:17:20,600
Wish you all the best.

2464
01:17:21,248 --> 01:17:22,960
Lin Yi said Steelie
is coming right away.

2465
01:17:23,360 --> 01:17:23,880
Really?

2466
01:17:23,880 --> 01:17:24,384
Yes.

2467
01:17:24,640 --> 01:17:25,200
You can go.

2468
01:17:25,600 --> 01:17:26,840
Xingxu, bye.

2469
01:17:26,840 --> 01:17:27,720
Don't miss me too much.

2470
01:17:27,720 --> 01:17:29,824
(You two, good luck)

2471
01:17:31,480 --> 01:17:32,160
Okay.

2472
01:17:32,192 --> 01:17:32,928
Not here yet?

2473
01:17:33,240 --> 01:17:33,480
Wait,

2474
01:17:33,480 --> 01:17:34,800
didn't your Steelie
say he was coming right away?

2475
01:17:34,800 --> 01:17:35,840
It's been half an hour.

2476
01:17:35,840 --> 01:17:38,080
(1.5 hours until scheduled dinner time)

2477
01:17:38,080 --> 01:17:39,840
Do you think they're already
in a bad situation?

2478
01:17:39,840 --> 01:17:40,880
They're already miserable enough.

2479
01:17:40,880 --> 01:17:41,680
I think so.

2480
01:17:41,680 --> 01:17:43,840
Jingfei, do you know if they got a ride?

2481
01:17:43,840 --> 01:17:44,760
They didn't get a ride.

2482
01:17:44,760 --> 01:17:45,952
We were on the phone
for a long time just now.

2483
01:17:45,952 --> 01:17:47,552
They only said that
because they couldn't get a ride.

2484
01:17:47,880 --> 01:17:49,360
No one stopped for them at all.

2485
01:17:49,360 --> 01:17:49,760
Of course.

2486
01:17:49,760 --> 01:17:50,360
Is that so?

2487
01:17:50,360 --> 01:17:50,720
Yes.

2488
01:17:50,720 --> 01:17:51,480
I don't think so.

2489
01:17:52,400 --> 01:17:53,840
Look, there are too many of them.

2490
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:55,552
Look, the people here
all drive small cars.

2491
01:17:55,584 --> 01:17:56,240
Right.

2492
01:17:56,240 --> 01:17:57,680
They'd need a sheep transporter
to fit them all.

2493
01:17:57,680 --> 01:17:58,360
Exactly.

2494
01:17:58,760 --> 01:17:59,640
People would think
why would the four of you

2495
01:17:59,640 --> 01:18:00,960
get in my car empty-handed?

2496
01:18:00,960 --> 01:18:01,504
Right.

2497
01:18:01,984 --> 01:18:02,480
Oh, no.

2498
01:18:02,480 --> 01:18:04,360
I think their fate

2499
01:18:05,040 --> 01:18:06,200
is hard to predict.

2500
01:18:06,200 --> 01:18:07,960
It's tough for them.

2501
01:18:07,960 --> 01:18:09,248
(One second of sympathy)

2502
01:18:09,248 --> 01:18:11,296
I'm still a bit worried about Naiwen.

2503
01:18:12,064 --> 01:18:13,760
(All's well, don't worry)

2504
01:18:14,560 --> 01:18:15,616
Hello, everybody.

2505
01:18:15,840 --> 01:18:17,560
Happy New Year. May you be prosperous.

2506
01:18:17,560 --> 01:18:18,880
Happy New Year.

2507
01:18:18,880 --> 01:18:19,280
Thank you.

2508
01:18:19,280 --> 01:18:20,040
Happy New Year.

2509
01:18:20,128 --> 01:18:21,696
Is this your first time in New Zealand?

2510
01:18:22,080 --> 01:18:23,040
Yes.

2511
01:18:23,040 --> 01:18:23,480
First time.

2512
01:18:23,480 --> 01:18:24,120
We're here for the first time.

2513
01:18:24,120 --> 01:18:25,080
First time.

2514
01:18:25,080 --> 01:18:25,920
Okay.

2515
01:18:26,880 --> 01:18:27,640
We're so lucky

2516
01:18:27,640 --> 01:18:28,800
to meet you.

2517
01:18:28,800 --> 01:18:29,472
Yes.

2518
01:18:29,472 --> 01:18:32,200
We've truly experienced

2519
01:18:32,200 --> 01:18:33,472
how hard it is to get a ride here.

2520
